condition: I did not want to tell my family how much I earn
condition_name: I did not want to tell my family how
message_text: It is completely normal to experience this. You don’t have to reveal the exact amount you earn; you could give an estimate. You could say, “In this household, we have this amount of money every month” rather than, “I make this amount of money”.

condition: When budgeting, we could not agree on what should fall under needs and what should fall under wants
condition_name: When budgeting, we could not agree o
message_text: It is completely normal to experience this challenge. People’s wants and needs are different sometimes. Talking about them together can help you and your family to understand each other, respect your differences, and see where you can compromise.

condition: I did not understand what to do

condition: My family did not want to do the budgeting with me
condition_name: My family did not want to do the bud
message_text: It is completely normal to experience this challenge. Try making the budget alone first and then try and include family members. Try reminding them that budgeting is important and it can help the family save money.
